name: contact
description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person. If no contact information is known, the value is the zero-length string.

name: name
description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name. If the name is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

name: location
description: The physical location of this node (e.g., 'telephone closet, 3rd floor'). If the location is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

name: services
description: A value which indicates the set of services that this entity may potentially offer. The value is a sum. This sum initially takes the value zero. Then, for each layer, L, in the range 1 through 7, that this node performs transactions for, 2 raised to (L - 1) is added to the sum. For example, a node which performs only routing functions would have a value of 4 (2^(3-1)). In contrast, a node which is a host offering application services would have a value of 72 (2^(4-1) + 2^(7-1)). Note that in the context of the Internet suite of protocols, values should be calculated accordingly: layer functionality 1 physical (e.g., repeaters) 2 datalink/subnetwork (e.g., bridges) 3 internet (e.g., supports the IP) 4 end-to-end (e.g., supports the TCP) 7 applications (e.g., supports the SMTP) For systems including OSI protocols, layers 5 and 6 may also be counted.

name: icmp echos
description: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages received. This object has been deprecated, as a new IP version-neutral table has been added. It is loosely replaced by a column in the icmpMsgStatsTable.

name: mac address
description: The interface's address at its protocol sub-layer. For example, for an 802.x interface, this object normally contains a MAC address. The interface's media-specific MIB must define the bit and byte ordering and the format of the value of this object. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.

name: ip incoming
description: The total number of input datagrams successfully delivered to IPv4 user-protocols (including ICMP). This object has been deprecated as a new IP version neutral table has been added. It is loosely replaced by ipSystemStatsIndelivers.

name: tcp active open
description: TCP in active open

name: UDP incoming
description: The total number of UDP datagrams delivered to UDP users. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by discontinuities in the value of sysUpTime.

name: Input 1 Voltage
description: The magnitude of the present input voltage (RMS).

name: Input 2 Voltage
description: The magnitude of the present input voltage (RMS).

name: Input 3 Voltage
description: The magnitude of the present input voltage (RMS).

name: Input 1 Current
description: The magnitude of the present input current.

name: Input 2 Current
description: The magnitude of the present input current.

name: Input 3 Current
description: The magnitude of the present input current.

name: Input 1 True Power
description: The magnitude of the present input true power.

name: Input 2 True Power
description: The magnitude of the present input true power.

name: Input 3 True Power
description: The magnitude of the present input true power.

name: Output source
description: The present source of output power. The enumeration none(2) indicates that there is no source of output power (and therefore no output power), for example, the system has opened the output breaker.

name: Output Frequency
description: The present output frequency.

name: Output 1 Voltage
description: The present output voltage (RMS).

name: Output 2 Voltage
description: The present output voltage (RMS).

name: Output 3 Voltage
description: The present output voltage (RMS).

name: Output 1 Current
description: The present output current (RMS).

name: Output 2 Current
description: The present output current (RMS).

name: Output 3 Current
description: The present output current (RMS).

name: Output 1 Power
description: The present output true power.

name: Output 2 Power
description: The present output true power.

name: Output 3 Power
description: The present output true power.

name: Output 1 Load %
description: The percentage of the UPS power capacity presently being used on this output line, i.e., the greater of the percent load of true power capacity and the percent load of VA.

name: Output 2 Load %
description: The percentage of the UPS power capacity presently being used on this output line, i.e., the greater of the percent load of true power capacity and the percent load of VA.

name: Output 3 Load %
description: The percentage of the UPS power capacity presently being used on this output line, i.e., the greater of the percent load of true power capacity and the percent load of VA.

name: Bypass Frequency
description: The present bypass frequency.

name: Bypass 1 voltage
description: The present bypass voltage (RMS).

name: Bypass 2 voltage
description: The present bypass voltage (RMS).

name: Bypass 3 voltage
description: The present bypass voltage (RMS).

name: Bypass 1 Current
description: The present bypass current (RMS).

name: Bypass 2 Current
description: The present bypass current (RMS).

name: Bypass 3 Current
description: The present bypass current (RMS).

name: Bypass 1 Power
description: The present true power conveyed by the bypass.

name: Bypass 2 Power
description: The present true power conveyed by the bypass.

name: Bypass 3 Power
description: The present true power conveyed by the bypass.

name: Battery status
description: The indication of the capacity remaining in the UPS system's batteries. A value of batteryNormal indicates that the remaining run-time is greater than upsConfigLowBattTime. A value of batteryLow indicates that the remaining battery run-time is less than or equal to upsConfigLowBattTime. A value of batteryDepleted indicates that the UPS will be unable to sustain the present load when and if the utility power is lost (including the possibility that the utility power is currently absent and the UPS is unable to sustain the output).

name: Battery time in Seconds
description: If the unit is on battery power, the elapsed time since the UPS last switched to battery power, or the time since the network management subsystem was last restarted, whichever is less. Zero shall be returned if the unit is not on battery power.
